.TH "ssam_device_alloc" 9 "ssam_device_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_device_alloc \- Allocate and initialize a SSAM client device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ssam_device *" ssam_device_alloc
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "struct ssam_device_uid uid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller under which the device should be added.
.IP "uid" 12
The UID of the device to be added.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates and initializes a new client device. The parent of the device
will be set to the controller device and the name will be set based on the
UID. Note that the device still has to be added via \fBssam_device_add\fP.
Refer to that function for more details.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns the newly allocated and initialized SSAM client device, or
NULL if it could not be allocated.
